message.content: For any natural number $n$ and any function $z$ from the finite type of size $n$ to the complex numbers $\mathbb{C}$, the absolute value of the real part of the square root of the sum of the squares of $z(i)$ is less than or equal to the sum of the absolute values of the real parts of $z(i)$ for all $i$.

The theorem states that for any natural number $n$ and any function $z$ mapping elements from a finite set of size $n$ to the complex numbers, the absolute value of the real part of the square root of the sum of squares of the function's outputs is less than or equal to the sum of the absolute values of the real parts of the outputs of the function.
